---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { breadcrumbSchema, webPageSchema, abs } from '../lib/seo';

const description =
  'Handout is the LearnHNS revival project for helping Handshake TLD owners publish real websites, DNSSEC, and DANE-secured names.';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Handout - Handshake TLD Hosting"
  description={description}
  keywords="Handout, Handshake hosting, HNS website, DNSSEC, DANE, TLSA, Knot DNS, nginx, iamthat"
  schema={[
    webPageSchema({ title: 'Handout - Handshake TLD Hosting', description, url: abs('/handout/') }),
    breadcrumbSchema([
      { name: 'Home', path: '/' },
      { name: 'Handout', path: '/handout/' },
    ]),
  ]}
>
  <div class="handout-page">
    <section class="hero-band">
      <div class="hero-copy">
        <p class="eyebrow">Live LearnHNS revival project</p>
        <h1>Handout helps a Handshake TLD become a working website.</h1>
        <p class="lede">
          Owning a Handshake name is only the first step. Handout is the open-source
          path we are reviving so a TLD owner can publish authoritative DNS,
          DNSSEC, DANE/TLSA, and web hosting without turning every launch into
          a custom sysadmin project.
        </p>
        <div class="actions">
          <a class="btn-primary" href="/handout/docs/iamthat-pilot/">Read the .iamthat pilot</a>
          <a class="btn-secondary" href="http://handout.iamthat/">Open handout.iamthat</a>
          <a class="btn-secondary" href="https://github.com/shadstoneofficial/handout" target="_blank" rel="noopener">View Handout repo</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <aside class="proof-panel" aria-label="Live Handout proof">
        <div class="browser-bar">
          <span></span>
          <span></span>
          <span></span>
          <code>http://handout.iamthat/</code>
        </div>
        <div class="browser-body">
          <p class="status">Live in SkyInclude Browser</p>
          <h2>handout.iamthat</h2>
          <p>First Handout-managed SLD for .iamthat.</p>
        </div>
      </aside>
    </section>

    <section class="story-section" id="pilot">
      <div class="section-kicker">The live story</div>
      <div class="story-grid">
        <article>
          <span>1</span>
          <h2>.iamthat is the root pilot.</h2>
          <p>
            We delegated the real Handshake TLD <code>.iamthat</code> to a
            Handout-managed server and confirmed it resolves through HNS-aware
            tooling.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article>
          <span>2</span>
          <h2>handout.iamthat is the first SLD.</h2>
          <p>
            The first subdomain was added through Handout's SLD review and
            guarded install flow, then checked in SkyInclude Browser.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article>
          <span>3</span>
          <h2>HTTP and HTTPS both stay enabled.</h2>
          <p>
            The first release should not force HTTPS redirects. HTTP keeps
            current HNS browsers and proxies usable, while HTTPS remains
            available for DANE/TLSA-capable clients.
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="split-section">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">What Handout owns</p>
        <h2>The technical pieces become a repeatable installer.</h2>
        <p>
          The revival release is centered on Knot authoritative DNS, nginx,
          DNSSEC signing, self-signed TLS certificates, TLSA records, parent
          record output for Bob or hsd, backups, rollback notes, and public
          proof artifacts.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="capability-list">
        <article>
          <strong>Authoritative DNS</strong>
          <p>Knot serves the TLD zone and managed SLD records.</p>
        </article>
        <article>
          <strong>DANE-first HTTPS</strong>
          <p>Self-signed certificates are paired with TLSA records instead of assuming Web2 CA trust.</p>
        </article>
        <article>
          <strong>Clean operations</strong>
          <p>Generated config is backed up, reviewable, and designed for uninstall or upgrade.</p>
        </article>
        <article>
          <strong>Manual parent safety</strong>
          <p>Bob or hsd publication remains a reviewed human step for now.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="hosted-section">
      <div class="hosted-copy">
        <p class="eyebrow">Next product question</p>
        <h2>Most people should not need to run the VPS themselves.</h2>
        <p>
          The open-source installer matters, but the community also needs a
          hosted Handout service: a simple dashboard where a TLD owner can add
          the Bob records once, create SLDs, publish starter pages, and grow
          into custom hosting later.
        </p>
        <div class="actions" style="margin-top: 2rem;">
          <a class="btn-primary" href="https://my.host.limo" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Sign up for Host.limo</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="hosted-steps">
        <article>
          <span>Owner</span>
          <p>Chooses a TLD and copies reviewed NS, GLUE4, and DS records into Bob.</p>
        </article>
        <article>
          <span>Handout</span>
          <p>Runs the DNS, DNSSEC, DANE, web server, backups, and proof checks.</p>
        </article>
        <article>
          <span>Community</span>
          <p>Gets real HNS websites without learning every infrastructure detail first.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .handout-page {
    max-width: 1120px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 1.5rem 4.5rem;
  }

  .hero-band {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1.05fr) minmax(320px, 0.95fr);
    gap: 2rem;
    align-items: center;
    padding: 4.5rem 0 3.25rem;
  }

  .eyebrow,
  .section-kicker,
  .status {
    color: var(--hns-violet);
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .hero-copy h1,
  .split-section h2,
  .hosted-copy h2 {
    font-size: clamp(2.2rem, 6vw, 4.6rem);
    letter-spacing: 0;
    margin-bottom: 1.1rem;
  }

  .split-section h2,
  .hosted-copy h2 {
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3.25rem);
  }

  .lede,
  .split-section p,
  .hosted-copy p {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    max-width: 680px;
  }

  .actions {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.8rem;
    margin-top: 1.6rem;
  }

  .proof-panel {
    border: 1px solid var(--glass-border-strong);
    border-radius: 8px;
    background: var(--surface);
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-card);
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .browser-bar {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: auto auto auto 1fr;
    gap: 0.45rem;
    align-items: center;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--glass-border);
    background: var(--surface-soft);
    padding: 0.85rem 1rem;
  }

  .browser-bar span {
    width: 10px;
    height: 10px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--glass-border-bright);
  }

  .browser-bar code {
    justify-self: end;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    overflow-wrap: anywhere;
  }

  .browser-body {
    min-height: 260px;
    padding: 2rem;
  }

  .browser-body h2 {
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3.4rem);
    letter-spacing: 0;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .browser-body p:last-child {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    font-size: 1.05rem;
  }

  .story-section,
  .split-section,
  .hosted-section {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--glass-border);
    padding: 3.25rem 0;
  }

  .story-grid,
  .capability-list,
  .hosted-steps {
    display: grid;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .story-grid {
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr));
  }

  .story-grid article,
  .capability-list article,
  .hosted-steps article {
    border: 1px solid var(--glass-border);
    border-radius: 8px;
    background: var(--surface);
    padding: 1.2rem;
  }

  .story-grid span,
  .hosted-steps span {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    min-width: 2rem;
    height: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.9rem;
    border-radius: 999px;
    background: rgba(105, 58, 250, 0.1);
    color: var(--hns-violet);
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  .story-grid h2 {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    letter-spacing: 0;
    margin-bottom: 0.65rem;
  }

  .story-grid p,
  .capability-list p,
  .hosted-steps p {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.65;
    margin: 0;
  }

  code {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    color: var(--hns-violet);
  }

  .split-section,
  .hosted-section {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 0.95fr) minmax(320px, 1.05fr);
    gap: 2rem;
    align-items: start;
  }

  .capability-list {
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
  }

  .capability-list strong {
    display: block;
    margin-bottom: 0.45rem;
  }

  .hosted-section {
    background: var(--surface-soft);
    border: 1px solid var(--glass-border);
    border-radius: 8px;
    margin-top: 1rem;
    padding: 2rem;
  }

  .hosted-steps {
    align-self: stretch;
  }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .hero-band,
    .story-grid,
    .split-section,
    .hosted-section,
    .capability-list {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .hero-band {
      padding-top: 3rem;
    }

    .hosted-section {
      padding: 1.25rem;
    }
  }
</style>
